Issues with Social Media

Social media has been affecting teens lives such as mental health, addicted to their phones, and cyberbullyhing

Mental Health

Many teens suffer from many mental health issues because of social media. The main part of of why is because of what they see on it. Many teens may be affected on their body images because of all these women who see many photos of perfect bodies and perfect lives. Social media can affect mental health because of cyberbullying and having to push themselves to fit the standards This link takes you to some effects to teens.

Addiction

Social media has increased the addiction of being on your phones, computers, and etc. Instagram, Snapchat, TikTok are a good example of social media that are mainly used by teens today. Many teens today now can't even stay that long without checking thier phones or messages. Here is a link to let you learn more about this issue

Cyberbullying

Cyberbullying again is one of the biggest reasons why teens suffer from their mental health. cyberbullying is a form of bullying through technology. This form of bullying is mainly seen in social media. Cyberbullying hurts many teens and makes them feel insecure with many things. Many teens mey get picked on based on their looks, lack of certain talent, and what they like. Many teens aren't able to be themsleves and suffer to please those who bully them. Cyberbullying is something that needs to stop. This affects many sad deaths from teens and depression.
